headline: General Dynamics (GD): Valuation Check After Double-Digit Earnings Growth and Record Defense Backlog
summary: General Dynamics (GD) just strung together several quarters of double digit earnings growth, backed by a record backlog and fresh U.S. Navy contracts, putting the stock squarely in focus for defense oriented investors. See our latest analysis for General Dynamics. All of this has helped keep momentum broadly positive, with the share price at about $335.80 and a strong year to date share price return of 28.7 percent alongside a solid multi year total shareholder return profile.
